<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910910-0037</DOCNO><DOCID>910910-0037.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Goodyear Tire andamp; Rubber Co.:   Polyester Business Is Offered   For Sale to Reduce Debt</HL><DATE>09/10/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C5</SO><CO>   GT</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)</IN><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)UNITED STATES (US)WEST VIRGINIA (WV)</RE><LP>   Goodyear Tire andamp; Rubber Co., Akron, Ohio, said it isseeking buyers for its entire polyester business as part ofits previously announced strategy of reducing debt with assetsales.   The polyester business, which makes resins for plasticbottles, trays and adhesives, employs 700 people, mostly inAkron and in Point Pleasant, W.Va.</LP><TEXT>   Stanley C. Gault, chairman, said in July that the tiremaker was seeking buyers for non-core assets to reduce its$3.7 billion debt. He didn't identify the businesses, butthey were believed at the time to include various plasticsand chemical businesses with an estimated value of about $750million. Goodyear later sold a polyester tire cord and fabricplant for $105 million.</TEXT></DOC>